From: 3090 team <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: 2026-05-19
Subject: [PATCH] qwen3_5: fall back to HF layer_types when sglang config class doesn't win

Sister patch to 035. After 035 exposed `Qwen3_5MoeForCausalLM` in
`EntryClass`, the bare text-only causal-LM load path actually runs —
and immediately hits a second bug during `make_layers`:

    AttributeError: 'Qwen3_5MoeTextConfig' object has no attribute
    'layers_block_type'

Same class name `Qwen3_5MoeTextConfig` exists in TWO places:

  - sglang `srt/configs/qwen3_5.py` line 119 — declares
    `model_type = "qwen3_5_moe_text"` and inherits the
    `layers_block_type` @property from `Qwen3NextConfig` (returns
    sglang's internal values: `"attention"` / `"linear_attention"`,
    computed from `full_attention_interval`).
  - HF transformers `models/qwen3_5_moe/configuration_qwen3_5_moe.py`
    — also declares `model_type = "qwen3_5_moe_text"`, ships
    `layer_types: list[str]` (HF naming: `"full_attention"` /
    `"linear_attention"`), no `layers_block_type` attribute.

sglang's config module never calls `AutoConfig.register("qwen3_5_moe_text", ...)`
(only `qwen3_asr`, `lfm2*` and a few others do this), so HF's class
wins the registry lookup and `AutoConfig.from_pretrained` returns the
HF object. The model code then reads `config.layers_block_type[idx]`
and `AttributeError`s.

The multimodal route stays fine because the top-level model_type is
`qwen3_5_moe` (or `qwen3_5`), where sglang's `Qwen3_5MoeConfig`
declares `sub_configs = {"text_config": Qwen3_5MoeTextConfig}` —
that sub_config CONSTRUCTOR uses sglang's class explicitly, so the
inner text config object has the @property.

Repro for the bare causal-LM path (post-patch-035 environment):

    MODEL=$MODELS_DIR/hf-mattbucci/Qwen3.6-35B-A3B-AWQ-CT \
    QUANT=compressed-tensors \
    ./scripts/launch.sh qwen36

Before this patch: server boots, model load begins, dies in
`make_layers` at `config.layers_block_type[idx]`.

The fix is a defensive read in `Qwen3_5ForCausalLM.get_layer` (line
~1057): prefer `layers_block_type` (sglang's path), fall back to
`layer_types` (HF's path), and translate HF's `"full_attention"`
value to sglang's `"attention"` so the lookup in
`ALL_DECODER_LAYER_TYPES` matches either way. No new config code,
no AutoConfig registration shenanigans.

R9700 cross-team note: their v0.5.11 source has the same shape; they
should mirror this whenever they pick up patch 035.

---
 python/sglang/srt/models/qwen3_5.py | 10 +++++++++-
 1 file changed, 9 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/python/sglang/srt/models/qwen3_5.py b/python/sglang/srt/models/qwen3_5.py
--- a/python/sglang/srt/models/qwen3_5.py
+++ b/python/sglang/srt/models/qwen3_5.py
@@ -1028,7 +1028,16 @@ class Qwen3_5ForCausalLM(nn.Module):

         # Decoder layers
         def get_layer(idx: int, prefix: str):
-            layer_type = config.layers_block_type[idx]
+            # sglang's Qwen3NextConfig exposes `layers_block_type` via @property
+            # with values "attention" / "linear_attention". HF transformers'
+            # Qwen3_5MoeTextConfig (which AutoConfig picks for the bare causal LM
+            # route — sglang's qwen3_5 configs never call AutoConfig.register)
+            # only has `layer_types` with HF's values "full_attention" /
+            # "linear_attention". Read either, normalize to sglang's keys.
+            layer_type_list = getattr(config, "layers_block_type", None) or config.layer_types
+            layer_type = layer_type_list[idx]
+            if layer_type == "full_attention":
+                layer_type = "attention"
             layer_class = ALL_DECODER_LAYER_TYPES[layer_type]
             if layer_type == "attention":
                 prefix = add_prefix("self_attn", prefix)
